"GitHub","email":"noreply@github.com","date":"2026-05-21T00:14:48Z"},"message":"[ci] Add an `TURBO_TASKS_AVAILABLE_PARALLELISM` environment variable that overrides `std::thread::available_parallelism` callsites (#93995)\n\nWe want to use this to potentially improve efficiency in e2e tests where\nwe're running many instances of Turbopack at once. By default,\nturbo-tasks will try to use every available CPU core.\n\n**This environment variable does not strictly limit Turbopack to using 4\ncores, it just restricts the number of main tokio worker threads and\nchanges how we shard dashmaps.**\n\nThis option will not make sense for the vast majority of users, it only\nmakes sense when you are running *many* instances of Turbopack at once,\nand the exact semantics are potentially confusing, as it is not a hard\nlimit.\n\n## Test Plan\n\nBuild vercel-site with this set to 1 and see a little over 100% CPU\nusage. Set it to 8 and see around 800% CPU usage.\n\n```\nTURBO_TASKS_AVAILABLE_PARALLELISM=1 pnpm next build --experimental-build-mode=compile\n```","tree":{"sha":"4c9d2bba77be9bb2f9d1c061e9f4ba2229493e13","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vercel/next.js/git/trees/4c9d2bba77be9bb2f9d1c061e9f4ba2229493e13"},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vercel/next.js/git/commits/80cb3447c172c9a406a0b2ffa27a7dc0e4e8fac3","comment_count":0,"verification":{"verified":true,"reason":"valid","signature":"-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\nwsFcBAABCAAQBQJqDk54CRC1aQ7uu5UhlAAAsQMQAJM9qtZTDrcO2iZ2zrMd0mG9\nzDmNaHl9Ma/O1xiB/zWp7wDDZJRa1OpRXoWlPR9ryO84QY/Utiq/j6udru/mLzQf\n4FkyM0C3jF7zzybN7cfm87S+xeE5Erqn99j/0O+MvOFeD3Cx44b6a6fNRnJSUL2i\nrpfIUpE9YSKPhXDuRLCfyS4PJbayZfN4DlQLjlvRMe99HEDYf4ffPKVnYRldx/BO\nTsoZWIOASzfmy48jKo3faHbOLhiYcFWGR7iMCY8k2sw15/lUD9GMTUSNR1B/dAjo\nLSo1VP87cJpjm/AxP7hF/AF0N/+P6VByqRMyf9NGQrfD7URPmAzl3G2QjXUXYCJN\nD4krsSeE8MTZRGEMawowsOOTa8RkkfUkbjw1EqMe97xhXEJXHDxO39iE7L69YC1i\n4C94+DUYjZAGwNqfk+jtJjRcSx4htZb616OkJvNnzVvNuJYOwsN3jswZta/hB7pi\nSsNMhpO7kZRUPJBzxhR1Z252cTnr0FvA9DCLACGdw7w/4N3ri2vGmmH27P12e0Li\nqJZFvpvjbBocarDwaoLLDdNRtJq+j9DjbrmeVcOhF5/1Tz5KDbcye+/vK9G3hsQk\n2NMMd6gqBYNPe6Db3Jb2rCRGpgP7Ybh0HxygnT9XOdgKQEjJFRYKoABDt+UUmXDc\n9mSeYwDwnCye2PyKY4tM\n=2T60\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----\n","payload":"tree 4c9d2bba77be9bb2f9d1c061e9f4ba2229493e13\nparent 7c4b0525eeb2c072941a53f19aa89b71ed6704b4\nauthor Benjamin Woodruff <benjamin.woodruff@vercel.com> 1779322488 -0700\ncommitter GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1779322488 -0700\n\n[ci] Add an `TURBO_TASKS_AVAILABLE_PARALLELISM` environment variable that overrides `std::thread::available_parallelism` callsites (#93995)\n\nWe want to use this to potentially improve efficiency in e2e tests where\nwe're running many instances of Turbopack at once. By default,\nturbo-tasks will try to use every available CPU core.\n\n**This environment variable does not strictly limit Turbopack to using 4\ncores, it just restricts the number of main tokio worker threads and\nchanges how we shard dashmaps.**\n\nThis option will not make sense for the vast majority of users, it only\nmakes sense when you are running *many* instances of Turbopack at once,\nand the exact semantics are potentially confusing, as it is not a hard\nlimit.\n\n## Test Plan\n\nBuild vercel-site with this set to 1 and see a little over 100% CPU\nusage. Set it to 8 and see around 800% CPU usage.\n\n```\nTURBO_TASKS_AVAILABLE_PARALLELISM=1 pnpm next build --experimental-build-mode=compile\n```","verified_at":"2026-05-21T00:14:48Z"}},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vercel/next.js/commits/80cb3447c172c9a406a0b2ffa27a7dc0e4e8fac3","html_url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/commit/80cb3447c172c9a406a0b2ffa27a7dc0e4e8fac3","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vercel/next.js/commits/80cb3447c172c9a406a0b2ffa27a7dc0e4e8fac3/comments","author":{"login":"bgw","id":180404,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE4MDQwNA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/180404?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bgw","html_u