s_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"parents":[{"sha":"5b6747ad3fd34ebcc409e3743b705524b420a122","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vercel/next.js/commits/5b6747ad3fd34ebcc409e3743b705524b420a122","html_url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/commit/5b6747ad3fd34ebcc409e3743b705524b420a122"}]},{"sha":"5b6747ad3fd34ebcc409e3743b705524b420a122","node_id":"C_kwDOBC3CitoAKDViNjc0N2FkM2ZkMzRlYmNjNDA5ZTM3NDNiNzA1NTI0YjQyMGExMjI","commit":{"author":{"name":"Hendrik Liebau","email":"mail@hendrik-liebau.de","date":"2026-05-20T23:01:16Z"},"committer":{"name":"GitHub","email":"noreply@github.com","date":"2026-05-20T23:01:16Z"},"message":"Prerender HTTP access fallbacks with Cache Components semantics (#93988)\n\nThe body of `if (cacheComponents)` in `prerenderToStream` is extracted\ninto a local helper, `prerenderWithCacheComponents(getPayload)`. The\ncatch-block error paths now route through that helper whenever Cache\nComponents is enabled, which means the legacy `prerender-legacy` store\nis no longer reachable from a Cache Components prerender.\n\nAs a result, `notFound()`, `forbidden()`, and `unauthorized()` recovery\nrenders the matching fallback boundary under `prerender` and\n`prerender-client` semantics. Dynamic API access in those boundaries —\nfor example `useSearchParams()` without a surrounding `<Suspense>` — now\nsurfaces as a blocking-route error instead of the legacy\n`BailoutToCSRError`.\n\nThe dev side will be handled in a follow-up. The prerender handling\ndiverged a bit from the dev rendering in #92231, and we'll likely need\nto re-align the dev rendering first.\n\n> [!TIP]\n> Best reviewed with hidden whitespace changes.","tree":{"sha":"696525644bf8b915713ea97d070702b0445e2290","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vercel/next.js/git/trees/696525644bf8b915713ea97d070702b0445e2290"},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vercel/next.js/git/commits/5b6747ad3fd34ebcc409e3743b705524b420a122","comment_count":0,"verification":{"verified":true,"reason":"valid","signature":"-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\nwsFcBAABCAAQBQJqDj08CRC1aQ7uu5UhlAAAehQQAAQhbPxndTfg9j/Ah7kDFdes\nfoVS9CagUOZ3uHbXulSA8SopReS1YRD/zS6c8kBdWYHqv2w+b0MAYLkRvQMxE1AV\nQM3nH+cSdaVlMnY6p6hxJGXf2bL5SdSZtLGHrFfvKxHd8DUf/uKUgEXrUwSFQNaG\n+R3vCBpoMZ/2o0nih0kUFDrO0ZCih9hI7C9v/2S0BrqLcYJEe++yfedy9n9V9iH4\nuK2bBd88tCVeZ81imlFbbYPRLa3/1vRI9z9WL5Nb60Pnm5SVVGhyaljrHgz6tnXd\ntsNTNVZbMBVUCELxmi/UWW1X6qQsR9xtdW3bdUqoRg0pY32Aa9c6Oxyhalhc9JDX\nRTW1Q3jT2tciRr5j2wM7CWMY1gHpneoGU9DnkkxgxqIn09327fxEu2WNBeFYbyFq\nfPns87klz0CJkVhbgrnba+WA+loz8HfJyz6sbF+20qw1uupcLK477cqa+c0nzNKt\nQx6uhU/Ku69oxpTr4ebLnf4FIVwyumrcj6fOFWZK4vZuSm4zVRRPo+BmF7qea3fn\ni4+ONKU1M+unEKuUpgCmOgepuQ948OqKaVHFFSY8hOxHDJUEDoP9ocSQZE9xXjQW\n+rvs5IYS4i01XNYOvaH24m5tYAnYr4rcBV3vi7j0GOVzxKp64HZrRnpNkwsXOkqd\n/fYXqFs0QU8vP3SAX7Vo\n=RCFF\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----\n","payload":"tree 696525644bf8b915713ea97d070702b0445e2290\nparent fda6986b264e1f01fad493fc9c174e7b2ac9919c\nauthor Hendrik Liebau <mail@hendrik-liebau.de> 1779318076 +0200\ncommitter GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1779318076 +0000\n\nPrerender HTTP access fallbacks with Cache Components semantics (#93988)\n\nThe body of `if (cacheComponents)` in `prerenderToStream` is extracted\ninto a local helper, `prerenderWithCacheComponents(getPayload)`. The\ncatch-block error paths now route through that helper whenever Cache\nComponents is enabled, which means the legacy `prerender-legacy` store\nis no longer reachable from a Cache Components prerender.\n\nAs a result, `notFound()`, `forbidden()`, and `unauthorized()` recovery\nrenders the matching fallback boundary under `prerender` and\n`prerender-client` semantics. Dynamic API access in those boundaries —\nfor example `useSearchParams()` without a surrounding `<Suspense>` — now\nsurfaces as a blocking-route error instead of the legacy\n`BailoutToCSRError`.\n\nThe dev side will be handled in a follow-up. The prerender handling\ndiverged a bit from the dev rendering in #92231, and we'll likely need\nto re-align the dev rendering first.\n\n> [!TIP]\n> Best reviewed with hidden whitespace changes.","verified_at":"2026-05-20T23:01:16Z"}},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vercel/next.js/commits/5b6747ad3fd34ebcc409e3743b705524b420a122","html_url":"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/commit/5b6747ad3fd34ebcc409e3743b705524b420a122","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vercel/next.js/commits/5b6747ad3fd34ebcc409e3743b705524b420a122/comments","author":{"login":"unstubbable","id":761683,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc2MTY4Mw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/761683?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/unstubbable","html_url":"https://github.com/unstubbable","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/unstubbable/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/unstubbable/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/unstubbable/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/unstubbable/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/unstubbable/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/unstubbable/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/unstubbable/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/unstubbable/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/unstubbable/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"committer":{"login":"web-flow","id":19864447,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE5ODY0NDQ3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/19864447?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow","html_url":"https://github.com/web-flow","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/use